  "texts": [
    "Each non-empty temporal window 𝑤 includes 𝑘 seconds of high-level events triggered by the inhabitant.",
    "The goal of an eXplainable Activity Recognition (XAR) model is to map each window to the most likely activity performed by the subject, and to an explanation in natural language.",
    "Let A = {𝑎 1, 𝑎 2,..., 𝑎 𝑚 } be the set of target activities.",
    "Let ℎ be an XAR model, taking in input a window 𝑤 and providing as output the most likely activity 𝑎 ∈ A performed by the subject, and a corresponding explanation 𝑒𝑥𝑝.",
    "Note that 𝑒𝑥𝑝 describes in natural language the high-level events 𝐸 𝑤 included in 𝑤 that are considered the most important to classify 𝑎 by ℎ, and possibly their temporal relationships."
  ],
